<paragraph blockId="3.[680,1229,696,912]" pageId="3">
<emphasis box="[680,954,696,720]" italics="true" pageId="3">
Discussão: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" authorityYear="2008" box="[797,954,696,720]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anoreina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piara" status="sp. nov.">Anoreina piara</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[971,1050,696,719]" pageId="3" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
distingue-se de 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bates, 1861)" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[680,905,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oreodera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis box="[680,760,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="3">A. nana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bates" box="[774,897,728,752]" pageId="3" pagination="147 - 152" refId="ref2613" refString="Bates, H. W. 1861. Contributions to an insect fauna of the Amazon Valley. Coleoptera: Longicornes. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 3, 8: 147 - 152." type="journal article" year="1861">Bates, 1861</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
e de 
<taxonomicName authority="(Martins &amp; Galileo, 2005)" baseAuthorityName="Martins &amp; Galileo" baseAuthorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Xenofrea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis box="[959,1103,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="3">A. triangularis</emphasis>
(Martins &amp; Galileo, 2005)
</taxonomicName>
pela faixa de pubescência branca, oblíqua, no meio dos élitros que nas duas espécies é contínua da margem à sutura. De 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bates, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Bates" baseAuthorityYear="1866" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Oreodera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biannulata">
<emphasis box="[1011,1149,824,848]" italics="true" pageId="3">A. biannulata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bates" pageId="3" pagination="425 - 435" refId="ref2651" refString="Bates, H. W. 1866. Contributions to an insect fauna of the Amazon Valley. Coleoptera: Longicornes. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 3, 17: 425 - 435." type="journal article" year="1866">Bates, 1866</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, além do padrão de colorido dos élitros, pelas antenas não aneladas.
</paragraph>
